Sunday Services:<p>Sunday Bible school at 9:45AM<P>Worship Service at 11:00AM<P>Cross Training at 6:30PM</b>
<td width=30><TD VALIGN="TOP" width="79%" align=center><h2><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Arial" COLOR="maroon"><b><I>RPC Upcoming Events</font></u></h2><br></tr>
<tr><td><td>
<BR><BR>
<center><b>MONTHLY SUNDAY EVEVING SCHEDULE AT RPC</center><br>
Sunday Evening “Cross-Training”</b>
<p>“Cross-Training” has in view the cross of Christ that we are to have in sight as we run the race set before us (Hebrews 12:1-3) and the cross of discipleship we are to take up as we follow Jesus Christ (Luke 9:23). &nbsp;On Sunday evenings at 6:30 p.m. RPC will conduct practical, biblical training using Power Point, handouts and interactive study of God’s Word, coupled with small group prayer. &nbsp;“Cross-Training” will be held the first, third and fourth Sundays of the month in the church sanctuary.
<p><b>RPC Supper Clubs</b>
<p>The <u>second</u> Sunday of each month opportunity is provided for RPC Supper Clubs to meet for the purpose of building community and cultivating prayer. &nbsp;The Supper Clubs gather in various homes for 90 minutes to 2 hours some time in afternoon or early evening to eat a simple meal together, to discuss questions related to the morning sermon and to pray together.
<p><b>“Worship Where We Are”</b>
<p>On those months that have a <u>fifth</u> Sunday, we will meet downstairs in Fellowship Hall for a covered-dish dinner. &nbsp;Following the dinner, we remain downstairs and hold a “Worship Where We Are” evening service, including sharing, song, supplication and study of God’s Word.
<p>
Note: &nbsp;This schedule will be adjusted according to special events and circumstances.
<p><br><br>

</tr>
<tr><td><td>&nbsp;<img src="chillws.jpg" align=right width=125 height=175><br><B>ATTENTION PARENTS! -</B>&nbsp;  --a<b><I> Children's Worship Service</i></b> is held at 11:00AM (concurrent with regular service) in the classroom next to the nursery upstairs.  Parents of children ages 4-9 are encouraged to include their children in the service designed especially to be meaningful to children in the worship of God.  Elements of the service are singing, a Bible story, prayer and a creative hands-on learning activity.<p>&nbsp;<P>
